<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Inheritance — Java</title>

<!-- SyncDeck bundled runtime CSS (includes Reveal core + shared plugin styles) -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../../runtime/syncdeck-reveal/dist/syncdeck-reveal.css">

<!-- Fonts -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,700;1,400&display=swap">

<!-- Shared CSA theme -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../theme.css">

<style>
/* ============================================================
   DECK-SPECIFIC STYLES — Inheritance
   ============================================================ */

/* Open-in-browser link card */
.link-card {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.6em;
  padding: 0.65em 1.3em;
  background: rgba(0,255,65,0.08);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,65,0.45);
  border-radius: 3px;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: var(--body);
  color: var(--phosphor);
  text-decoration: none;
  transition: background 0.18s, border-color 0.18s;
}
.link-card:hover {
  background: rgba(0,255,65,0.15);
  border-color: var(--phosphor);
  color: var(--phosphor);
}
.link-card::before { content: '⬡ '; font-size: 0.85em; }

/* UML class diagram nodes */
.uml-node {
  background: var(--bg-card);
  border: 1px solid var(--phosphor-border);
  border-radius: 3px;
  padding: 0.35em 1.1em;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 18px;
  color: var(--text);
  text-align: center;
  min-width: 140px;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.uml-node.hi-p {
  border-color: var(--phosphor);
  color: var(--phosphor);
  background: rgba(0,255,65,0.07);
}
.uml-node.hi-a {
  border-color: var(--amber);
  color: var(--amber);
  background: rgba(255,224,51,0.07);
  font-style: italic;
}
.uml-node .stereo {
  display: block;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--amber-dim);
  font-style: italic;
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin-bottom: 0.15em;
}
/* Vertical chain connector */
.uml-vconn {
  width: 1px;
  height: 22px;
  background: var(--phosphor-border);
  margin: 0 auto;
  position: relative;
}
.uml-vconn::after {
  content: '▽';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: -14px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  color: var(--phosphor-dim);
  font-size: 13px;
}
/* Vertical chain layout */
.uml-chain {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0;
}
/* Horizontal children row with connecting lines */
.uml-children-wrap {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}
.uml-hbar-row {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 0;
}
.uml-child-col {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}
.uml-child-col .uml-vdown {
  width: 1px;
  height: 20px;
  background: var(--phosphor-border);
}

/* IS-A / HAS-A legend */
.diagram-legend {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--gap-lg);
  margin-top: var(--gap);
  font-size: 17px;
  color: var(--text-dim);
}
.legend-item {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5em;
}
.legend-line {
  width: 28px;
  height: 2px;
  background: var(--phosphor-border);
  position: relative;
}
.legend-line.dashed {
  background: none;
  border-top: 1px dashed rgba(0,255,65,0.35);
}
.legend-line::after {
  content: '▷';
  position: absolute;
  right: -8px;
  top: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  font-size: 10px;
  color: var(--phosphor-dim);
}

/* MCQ display (for showing answers on code inspection slide) */
.mcq-opts {
  list-style: none;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--gap-sm);
  margin-top: var(--gap);
}
.mcq-opts li {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: var(--gap-sm);
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: var(--body);
  color: var(--text-muted);
}
.opt-key {
  display: inline-block;
  min-width: 2.2em;
  padding: 0.1em 0.45em;
  background: rgba(0,255,65,0.07);
  border: 1px solid var(--phosphor-border);
  border-radius: 2px;
  font-size: 0.8em;
  color: var(--phosphor);
  font-weight: 700;
  text-align: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
.opt-correct { color: var(--green); }
.opt-wrong   { color: var(--red); opacity: 0.7; }

/* Error / warning callout boxes */
.err-box {
  background: rgba(255,77,106,0.06);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,77,106,0.4);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--red);
  border-radius: 3px;
  padding: 0.65em 1em;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: var(--small);
  color: var(--red);
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.warn-box {
  background: rgba(255,224,51,0.05);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255,224,51,0.35);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
  border-radius: 3px;
  padding: 0.65em 1em;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: var(--small);
  color: var(--amber);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* Horizontal rule separator */
.rule { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--phosphor-border); margin: var(--gap-sm) 0; }

/* Practice slide pizza circle */
.pizza-circle {
  width: 180px;
  height: 180px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255,149,0,0.18) 0%, rgba(255,149,0,0.04) 70%);
  border: 2px solid rgba(255,149,0,0.5);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 56px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="reveal">
<div class="slides">


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 01 · TITLE
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:600px;height:600px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.11) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-200px;left:-140px;"></div>
  <div class="glow" style="width:400px;height:400px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-80px;right:6%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner slide-center">
    <span class="slide-tag">AP CSA · Unit 9</span>

    <h1 class="title-h1">
      <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Inherit</span><span>ance</span>
    </h1>

    <p style="font-size:28px;color:var(--text-dim);margin-top:var(--gap);">Passing down the riches</p>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 02 · REAL-WORLD INHERITANCE
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:450px;height:450px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.10) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;right:5%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Concept</span>
    <h2>What is <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Inheritance</span>?</h2>

    <ul class="bullets" style="max-width:780px;gap:0.45em;">
      <li class="fragment fade-up">In the real world, wealth passes from generation to generation</li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">Children inherit their parents' possessions</li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        In computer science, the "wealth" is <strong style="color:var(--text);">data</strong> and <strong style="color:var(--text);">methods</strong>
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        Big advantage: <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">computers can share without the "death" part!</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout accent-p fragment fade-up" style="max-width:680px;margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">
      Objects can be built <em>on top of</em> other objects, inheriting their features while adding new ones.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 03 · CLASSES ARE BLUEPRINTS
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-80px;left:5%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Concept</span>
    <h2>Classes are like <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">blueprints</span></h2>

    <ul class="bullets" style="max-width:780px;gap:0.45em;">
      <li class="fragment fade-up">A house blueprint describes how to build a house</li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">Many houses can be built from the same blueprint</li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        Each house is its own <strong style="color:var(--text);">instance</strong> — different colors, addresses, furniture…
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout accent-a fragment fade-up" style="max-width:720px;margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">
      <strong style="color:var(--amber);">Think about it:</strong> Would you throw out the whole blueprint and start over just to add a bigger garage?
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 04 · EXTENDING THE PLAN
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:500px;height:500px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.10) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-150px;right:-80px;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Concept</span>
    <h2><span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Extending</span> the plan</h2>

    <p style="font-size:var(--body);color:var(--text-muted);max-width:760px;line-height:1.7;">
      Instead of starting from scratch, you <em>modify</em> the blueprint — keep all the good parts, override only what needs to change, and add anything new.
    </p>

    <div class="callout accent-p" style="max-width:760px;margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">
      <strong style="color:var(--phosphor);">Definition:</strong>
      <span style="color:var(--text-muted);"> Inheritance is all about <strong style="color:var(--text);">extending</strong> the concept represented by a class by adding or changing features, while keeping all the existing features.</span>
    </div>

    <div class="split" style="margin-top:var(--gap-lg);gap:var(--gap);">
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--gap-sm);">
        <p style="font-size:17px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;">Superclass (parent)</p>
        <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:20px;">Rectangle</div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;font-size:28px;color:var(--phosphor-dim);padding-top:1.4em;">→</div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--gap-sm);">
        <p style="font-size:17px;color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;">Subclass (child)</p>
        <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:20px;">Square</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 05 · YOU'VE SEEN THIS ALREADY
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:550px;height:550px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.08) 0%,transparent 70%);top:50%;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner slide-center">
    <span class="slide-tag">Recall</span>
    <h2>You've <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">already</span> experienced this</h2>

    <p style="font-size:var(--body);color:var(--text-muted);max-width:680px;line-height:1.7;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      You've already used inheritance in Java.<br>
      Don't remember? Think <em>waaaay</em> back…
    </p>

    <p class="fragment fade-up" style="font-size:36px;color:var(--amber);margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">🧟 Remember Karl?</p>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 06 · KARL IS A ZOMBIE — class hierarchy diagram
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;left:0%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Review</span>
    <h2>Karl is a <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Zombie</span></h2>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:center;">

      <!-- Left: explanation bullets -->
      <ul class="bullets" style="gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--small);">
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          <strong style="color:var(--text);">Zombie</strong> — basic capabilities: move forward, turn right
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          <strong style="color:var(--text);">UltraZombie extends Zombie</strong> — adds turn left, face directions
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          <strong style="color:var(--text);">MyZombie extends UltraZombie</strong> — your custom extensions
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up" style="color:var(--phosphor);">
          New skills added — old skills <em>kept</em>
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          ZombieLand EXTENDED Karl's capabilities with new skills
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Right: UML vertical chain -->
      <div class="uml-chain" style="gap:0;">
        <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:18px;">Actor</div>
        <div class="uml-vconn"></div>
        <div style="height:22px;"></div>
        <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:18px;">Zombie</div>
        <div class="uml-vconn"></div>
        <div style="height:22px;"></div>
        <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:18px;">UltraZombie</div>
        <div class="uml-vconn"></div>
        <div style="height:22px;"></div>
        <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:18px;">MyZombie</div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="diagram-legend fragment fade-up">
      <div class="legend-item">
        <div class="legend-line"></div>
        <span>IS-A (inherits from)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 07 · THE extends KEYWORD
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.10) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-120px;right:4%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Java</span>
    <h2>The <code>extends</code> keyword</h2>

    <div class="code-card" style="width:100%;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <div class="code-hdr">
        <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
        <span class="clang">Java</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-body">
        <pre><span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">MyZombie</span> <span class="kw">extends</span> <span class="tp">UltraZombie</span> {
  <span class="cm">// MyZombie has all the power of UltraZombie, and then some</span>
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <ul class="bullets" style="max-width:800px;gap:0.45em;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        <code>extends</code> means: "MyZombie has all the power of UltraZombie, <em>and then some</em>"
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        Calling <code>move()</code> on MyZombie works — even though MyZombie never defined it
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        MyZombie inherited a whole pile of methods from the chain:<br>
        <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">UltraZombie → Zombie → Actor → Object</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 08 · RECTANGLE / SQUARE EXAMPLE — runnable link
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-60px;left:3%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Example</span>
    <h2>A new example: <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Rectangle</span> &amp; Square</h2>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;margin-top:var(--gap);">

      <!-- Left: class list + key points -->
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--gap);">
        <p style="font-size:var(--small);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;color:var(--text-dim);">Three classes</p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--gap-sm);">
          <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:18px;">Main</div>
          <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:18px;">Rectangle</div>
          <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:18px;">Square<br><span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--phosphor-dim);">extends Rectangle</span></div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.6;">
          Square reuses all of Rectangle's methods — <code>getWidth()</code>, <code>getHeight()</code>, <code>getArea()</code>, <code>getPerimeter()</code>…
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: code preview -->
      <div class="code-card" style="flex:1;">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
          <span class="clang">Square.java</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          <pre><span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">Square</span> <span class="kw">extends</span> <span class="tp">Rectangle</span> {

  <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>(<span class="kw">double</span> side) {
    <span class="kw">super</span>(side, side); <span class="cm">// call Rectangle(w,h)</span>
    setName(<span class="nm">"Square"</span>);
  }

  <span class="kw">public double</span> getSideLength() {
    <span class="kw">return super</span>.getWidth();
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:var(--gap-lg);display:flex;gap:var(--gap);">
      <a class="link-card"
         href="https://run.mycode.run/?runlocal=true&noproject=true&nofiles=true&code=XQAAAQDrBAAAAAAAAAAtiIpHPJkiDSD3eirckGfVDlyCzGKafDiNdzYcptq24WYsABZXK1m1qc4UVyDjDdEKGWF8ybteMLx7oJeIiuj2%2BC0JTF8n0Bkzl5Hk5tpMCcSGP4h7OM%2FWPk35eipz6uKBfhQN4EiMF%2B%2BIgdCzfJWBUJLp3VnXc8iIBb4wGflEVIAFNnlR6NNhHhYakHmcWiNJ%2FHMNIuUhGWnQaZScPdTPlrDDSq%2FzAl9qhEDuP%2BzZkpO%2BVo9OGqHp8q2F0H6jHg%2B9dOQfaVXi%2BuXm4Bnm1Cxl5B2%2FZ2HbOPiE%2Bc2fj"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Open in browser →
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box fragment fade-up" style="margin-top:var(--gap);max-width:620px;">
      <strong>Note:</strong> <code>super</code> isn't technically required in <code>getSideLength()</code> if Square doesn't define its own <code>getWidth()</code> — but it's good style to be explicit.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 09 · CODE INSPECTION — Resonance (free-response)
     ============================================================ -->
<section
  data-activity-id="resonance"
  data-activity-trigger="slide-enter"
  data-activity-instance-key="resonance:8:0"
  data-activity-options='{"questions":[{"id":"q1","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Square s = new Square(5);  Select ALL methods you can call on s.","order":0,"options":[{"id":"q1a","text":"s.getSideLength()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1b","text":"s.getWidth()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1c","text":"s.getArea()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1d","text":"s.getPerimeter()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1e","text":"s.getName()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1f","text":"s.getRadius()","isCorrect":false}]}]}'>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;right:6%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Code Inspection</span>
    <h2>Which methods can you <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">use</span>?</h2>

    <div class="code-card" style="max-width:500px;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <div class="code-hdr">
        <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
        <span class="clang">Java</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-body">
        <pre><span class="tp">Square</span> s = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>(<span class="nm">5</span>);</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Answer — revealed after discussion -->
    <div class="fragment fade-up" style="margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;margin-bottom:var(--gap-sm);">▸ All inherited methods work — <code>getRadius()</code> never existed:</p>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:var(--gap-sm) var(--gap-lg);max-width:720px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--body);">
          <span style="color:var(--green);">✓</span> <code>s.getSideLength()</code> <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);">Square</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--body);">
          <span style="color:var(--green);">✓</span> <code>s.getPerimeter()</code> <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);">Rectangle</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--body);">
          <span style="color:var(--green);">✓</span> <code>s.getWidth()</code> <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);">Rectangle</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--body);">
          <span style="color:var(--green);">✓</span> <code>s.getArea()</code> <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);">Rectangle</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--body);">
          <span style="color:var(--green);">✓</span> <code>s.getName()</code> <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);">Rectangle</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:0.5em;font-size:var(--body);">
          <span style="color:var(--red);">✗</span> <code>s.getRadius()</code> <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--red);">doesn't exist</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 10 · BACKGROUND — The Object class
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-120px;left:2%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Background</span>
    <h2>All classes extend <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Object</span></h2>

    <ul class="bullets" style="max-width:800px;gap:0.45em;">
      <li class="fragment fade-up">All Java code must be inside a class</li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">Every class extends exactly <strong style="color:var(--text);">one</strong> other class</li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        If you write no <code>extends</code> clause, Java automatically extends <code>Object</code>
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        <code>Object</code> is the superclass of every class in Java
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        This is why <em>every</em> object has a <code>toString()</code> method by default
        <br><span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);">e.g., <code>MyClass@4F3C56</code></span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="code-card" style="max-width:680px;margin-top:var(--gap-lg);" >
      <div class="code-hdr">
        <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
        <span class="clang">Java</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-body">
        <pre><span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">MyClass</span> { }
<span class="cm">// Java treats this as:</span>
<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">MyClass</span> <span class="kw">extends</span> <span class="tp">Object</span> { } <span class="cm">// implicit</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 11 · IMPLICATIONS OF INHERITANCE
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-60px;right:4%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Rules</span>
    <h2>What subclasses <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">get</span></h2>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;margin-top:var(--gap);">

      <div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--small);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;color:var(--green);margin-bottom:var(--gap-sm);">✓ Subclasses can…</p>
        <ul class="bullets" style="gap:0.45em;font-size:var(--small);">
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Inherit all public &amp; protected methods and fields from every ancestor</li>
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Add new fields and methods</li>
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Override existing methods (change behavior)</li>
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Call parent methods and constructors via <code>super</code></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--small);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;color:var(--red);margin-bottom:var(--gap-sm);">✗ Subclasses cannot…</p>
        <ul class="bullets" style="gap:0.45em;font-size:var(--small);">
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Directly access <code>private</code> members of their parent</li>
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Remove inherited methods or fields</li>
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Make an inherited method less visible (e.g., public → private)</li>
          <li class="fragment fade-up">Directly set up private members of ancestors in their own constructor</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 12 · CONSTRUCTORS
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;right:5%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Constructors</span>
    <h2>Constructors are <span style="color:var(--amber);">special</span></h2>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;margin-top:var(--gap);">

      <ul class="bullets" style="gap:0.45em;font-size:var(--small);">
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Classes do <strong>NOT</strong> inherit their parent's constructors</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Exception: if you write no constructor and parent has a default (no-arg) constructor, that one is used</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Call a parent constructor with <code>super(...)</code> — <strong>must be the first line</strong></li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">If you don't call <code>super()</code>, the parent's no-arg constructor runs automatically first</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Cannot call both <code>super()</code> and <code>this()</code> — you must pick one</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="code-card" style="flex:1;">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
          <span class="clang">Square.java</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          <pre><span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>
    <span class="kw">extends</span> <span class="tp">Rectangle</span> {

  <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>(<span class="kw">double</span> side) {
    <span class="cm">// MUST be first line:</span>
    <span class="kw">super</span>(side, side);
    setName(<span class="nm">"Square"</span>);
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 13 · OVERRIDING METHODS
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-80px;left:3%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Overriding</span>
    <h2><span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Overriding</span> methods</h2>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;margin-top:var(--gap);">

      <ul class="bullets" style="gap:0.45em;font-size:var(--small);">
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Any method not marked <code>final</code> can be overridden</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Must have the <strong style="color:var(--text);">exact same signature</strong> — name + parameter types</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Different parameters = <em>overloading</em>, not overriding</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Use <code>@Override</code> — Java will verify you're really overriding</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Overriding <strong>replaces</strong> the parent's behavior</li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">Can augment parent behavior: call <code>super.methodName(…)</code> then add more</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="code-card" style="flex:1;">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
          <span class="clang">Java</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          <pre><span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">Dog</span> <span class="kw">extends</span> <span class="tp">Animal</span> {

  <span class="nm">@Override</span>
  <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">String</span> talk() {
    <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">"Woof!"</span>;
  }
}

<span class="kw">public class</span> <span class="tp">GuideDog</span> <span class="kw">extends</span> <span class="tp">Dog</span> {

  <span class="nm">@Override</span>
  <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">String</span> talk() {
    <span class="cm">// augment parent</span>
    <span class="kw">return super</span>.talk() + <span class="nm">" (friendly)"</span>;
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 14 · THE super KEYWORD
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.10) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-120px;right:3%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">super</span>
    <h2>The <code>super</code> keyword</h2>

    <ul class="bullets" style="max-width:800px;gap:0.5em;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        Used to access something from the <strong style="color:var(--text);">superclass</strong> that the subclass has overridden
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        <code>super.methodName(…)</code> — calls the <em>parent's</em> version of a method
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        <code>super(…)</code> — in a constructor, calls the parent's constructor
      </li>
      <li class="fragment fade-up">
        <code>super.fieldName</code> — access a parent field (if not hidden)
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="err-box fragment fade-up" style="max-width:620px;margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">
      <strong>Not allowed:</strong> Java does not support nested supers.<br>
      <code>super.super.methodName()</code> is a compile error.
    </div>

    <div class="callout accent-p fragment fade-up" style="max-width:680px;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <code>super</code> is your bridge to the parent — use it when you want the original behavior, not the overridden one.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 15 · ABSTRACT CLASSES
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-60px;right:5%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Abstract</span>
    <h2><span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Abstract</span> classes</h2>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;margin-top:var(--gap);">

      <ul class="bullets" style="gap:0.45em;font-size:var(--small);">
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          Describes the behaviors of a type — but <strong>cannot be instantiated</strong>
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          Used when the concept is real, but there's no sensible "generic" version
          <span style="color:var(--text-dim);">(what does a generic Shape look like?)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          Can contain <strong>abstract methods</strong> — signature only, no body
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          If a method is <code>abstract</code>, its class <strong>must</strong> also be <code>abstract</code>
        </li>
        <li class="fragment fade-up">
          Subclasses must implement all abstract methods — or also be declared abstract
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="code-card" style="flex:1;">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
          <span class="clang">Shape.java</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          <pre><span class="kw">public abstract class</span> <span class="tp">Shape</span> {

  <span class="kw">private</span> <span class="tp">String</span> name;

  <span class="cm">// All shapes HAVE an area,</span>
  <span class="cm">// but it's calculated differently</span>
  <span class="kw">public abstract double</span> getArea();

  <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">String</span> getName() {
    <span class="kw">return</span> name;
  }
  <span class="kw">public void</span> setName(<span class="tp">String</span> n) {
    name = n;
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="err-box fragment fade-up" style="margin-top:var(--gap);max-width:500px;">
      <code>Shape s = new Shape();</code> &nbsp;← compile error! Cannot instantiate abstract class.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 16 · SHAPES FRAMEWORK — class hierarchy diagram
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;left:5%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Example</span>
    <h2>The <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Shapes</span> Framework</h2>

    <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:var(--gap-lg);">All shapes share a base — each subclass adds what makes it unique.</p>

    <!-- Shapes hierarchy diagram -->
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0;">

      <!-- Root: Shape -->
      <div class="uml-node hi-a" style="font-size:19px;">
        <span class="stereo">&lt;&lt;abstract&gt;&gt;</span>
        Shape
      </div>

      <!-- Connector down -->
      <div style="width:1px;height:20px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
      <!-- Horizontal bar -->
      <div style="display:flex;gap:0;align-items:flex-start;border-top:1px solid rgba(0,255,65,0.2);padding-top:0;width:640px;">
        <!-- Column: Ellipse → Circle -->
        <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0;padding-top:0;">
          <div style="width:1px;height:20px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
          <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:17px;">Ellipse</div>
          <div style="width:1px;height:16px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
          <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:17px;min-width:110px;">Circle</div>
        </div>
        <!-- Column: Rectangle → Square -->
        <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0;">
          <div style="width:1px;height:20px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
          <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:17px;">Rectangle</div>
          <div style="width:1px;height:16px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
          <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:17px;min-width:110px;">Square</div>
        </div>
        <!-- Column: Triangle -->
        <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0;">
          <div style="width:1px;height:20px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
          <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:17px;">Triangle</div>
        </div>
        <!-- Column: Polygon -->
        <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0;">
          <div style="width:1px;height:20px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
          <div class="uml-node" style="font-size:17px;">Polygon</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div style="display:flex;gap:var(--gap-lg);margin-top:var(--gap-lg);font-size:17px;color:var(--text-dim);">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5em;">
        <div style="width:28px;height:1px;background:var(--amber-dim);"></div>
        <span style="color:var(--amber);">&lt;&lt;abstract&gt;&gt;</span> = cannot instantiate
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5em;">
        <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Highlighted</span> = leaf classes (no children)
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 17 · INHERITANCE AND ASSIGNMENT
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.10) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-120px;right:3%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Polymorphism</span>
    <h2>Inheritance and <span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Assignment</span></h2>

    <p style="font-size:var(--body);color:var(--text-muted);max-width:760px;line-height:1.7;">
      Because of inheritance, you can assign a subclass object to a superclass variable — and then hold different subclass objects in the same variable over time.
    </p>

    <div class="code-card" style="max-width:700px;margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">
      <div class="code-hdr">
        <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
        <span class="clang">Java</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-body">
        <pre><span class="cm">// All valid assignments:</span>
<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">String</span>&gt; myList = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();  <span class="fragment fade-up cm" data-fragment-index="1">// ArrayList IS-A List</span>

<span class="tp">Actor</span> player = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Ghost</span>();              <span class="fragment fade-up cm" data-fragment-index="2">// Ghost IS-A Actor</span>

<span class="tp">Rectangle</span> r = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>(<span class="nm">15</span>);           <span class="fragment fade-up cm" data-fragment-index="3">// Square IS-A Rectangle</span>

<span class="tp">Shape</span> s = r;                              <span class="fragment fade-up cm" data-fragment-index="4">// Rectangle IS-A Shape</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 18 · ASSIGNMENT DIRECTION + CASTING
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,77,106,0.07) 0%,transparent 70%);bottom:-60px;left:3%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Casting</span>
    <h2>Assignment goes <span style="color:var(--amber);">one direction</span></h2>

    <div class="callout accent-a" style="max-width:680px;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      "All squares are rectangles, but not all rectangles are squares."
    </div>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;margin-top:var(--gap);">

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--gap-sm);">
        <p style="font-size:17px;color:var(--green);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;">✓ Valid</p>
        <div class="code-card">
          <div class="code-hdr">
            <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
            <span class="clang">Java</span>
          </div>
          <div class="code-body">
            <pre><span class="tp">Rectangle</span> r = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>(<span class="nm">15</span>);
<span class="tp">Shape</span> s = r;</pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-muted);">Subclass → superclass always works</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--gap-sm);">
        <p style="font-size:17px;color:var(--red);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;">✗ Compile Error</p>
        <div class="code-card">
          <div class="code-hdr">
            <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
            <span class="clang">Java</span>
          </div>
          <div class="code-body">
            <pre><span class="tp">Square</span> sq = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Rectangle</span>(<span class="nm">5</span>, <span class="nm">6</span>);
<span class="cm">// Cannot assign superclass → subclass</span></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-muted);">Not all rectangles are squares!</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Casting -->
    <div class="fragment fade-up" style="margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <p style="font-size:var(--small);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;color:var(--text-dim);margin-bottom:var(--gap-sm);">▸ Force it with a cast (if you <em>know</em> the type)</p>
      <div class="code-card" style="max-width:660px;">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
          <span class="clang">Java</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          <pre><span class="tp">Rectangle</span> r = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Square</span>(<span class="nm">15</span>);
<span class="tp">Shape</span> s = r;
<span class="tp">Square</span> sq = (<span class="tp">Square</span>) s;   <span class="cm">// ok — s IS a Square</span>

<span class="tp">Rectangle</span> bad = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Rectangle</span>(<span class="nm">5</span>, <span class="nm">6</span>);
<span class="tp">Square</span> err = (<span class="tp">Square</span>) bad; <span class="cm">// ClassCastException at runtime!</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 19 · RESONANCE MCQ — Shape assignment
     ============================================================ -->
<section
  data-activity-id="resonance"
  data-activity-trigger="slide-enter"
  data-activity-instance-key="resonance:18:0"
  data-activity-options='{"questions":[{"id":"q1","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Shape s = new Rectangle(15);  Select ALL of the following that you can call on s without a compile error.","order":0,"options":[{"id":"q1a","text":"s.getHeight()","isCorrect":false},{"id":"q1b","text":"s.getWidth()","isCorrect":false},{"id":"q1c","text":"s.toString()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1d","text":"s.setName(\"x\")","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1e","text":"s.getName()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1f","text":"s.getArea()","isCorrect":true},{"id":"q1g","text":"s.getSideLength()","isCorrect":false}]}]}'>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,224,51,0.09) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-100px;right:5%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Check Your Understanding</span>
    <h2>What can you do with <code style="color:var(--phosphor);">s</code>?</h2>

    <div class="code-card" style="max-width:480px;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      <div class="code-hdr">
        <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
        <span class="clang">Java</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-body">
        <pre><span class="tp">Shape</span> s = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Rectangle</span>(<span class="nm">15</span>);</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Answer revealed after discussion -->
    <div class="fragment fade-up" style="margin-top:var(--gap-lg);">
      <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.12em;margin-bottom:var(--gap-sm);">▸ <code>s</code> is declared as <code>Shape</code> — you only get what Shape (and Object) provide:</p>
      <ul class="mcq-opts" style="max-width:600px;">
        <li><span class="opt-key">A</span> <code class="opt-wrong">s.getHeight()</code>   <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--red);"> ✗ — not on Shape</span></li>
        <li><span class="opt-key">B</span> <code class="opt-wrong">s.getWidth()</code>    <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--red);"> ✗ — not on Shape</span></li>
        <li><span class="opt-key">C</span> <code class="opt-correct">s.toString()</code>  <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);"> ✓ — from Object</span></li>
        <li><span class="opt-key">D</span> <code class="opt-correct">s.setName("x")</code><span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);"> ✓ — from Shape</span></li>
        <li><span class="opt-key">E</span> <code class="opt-correct">s.getName()</code>   <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);"> ✓ — from Shape</span></li>
        <li><span class="opt-key">F</span> <code class="opt-correct">s.getArea()</code>   <span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);"> ✓ — abstract in Shape</span></li>
        <li><span class="opt-key">G</span> <code class="opt-wrong">s.getSideLength()</code><span style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--red);"> ✗ — not on Shape</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     SLIDE 20 · POLYMORPHISM
     ============================================================ -->
<section>
  <div class="glow" style="width:440px;height:440px;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(0,255,65,0.10) 0%,transparent 70%);top:-120px;left:3%;"></div>

  <div class="slide-inner">
    <span class="slide-tag">Polymorphism</span>
    <h2><span style="color:var(--phosphor);">Polymorphism</span></h2>

    <p style="font-size:var(--small);color:var(--text-dim);margin-bottom:var(--gap);">
      <em>poly</em> = many &nbsp;·&nbsp; <em>morph</em> = form &nbsp;·&nbsp; same method call, different behavior depending on the actual object
    </p>

    <div class="split" style="gap:var(--gap-lg);align-items:start;">

      <!-- Class diagram: Animal hierarchy -->
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:0;">
        <div class="uml-node hi-a" style="font-size:18px;">
          <span class="stereo">&lt;&lt;abstract&gt;&gt;</span>
          Animal
          <span style="font-size:13px;color:var(--phosphor-dim);display:block;margin-top:0.2em;">+ talk() : String</span>
        </div>
        <div style="width:1px;height:18px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:0;border-top:1px solid rgba(0,255,65,0.2);width:360px;">
          <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;">
            <div style="width:1px;height:18px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
            <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:16px;min-width:70px;">Cow</div>
          </div>
          <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;">
            <div style="width:1px;height:18px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
            <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:16px;min-width:70px;">Dog</div>
          </div>
          <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;">
            <div style="width:1px;height:18px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
            <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:16px;min-width:70px;">Pig</div>
          </div>
          <div style="flex:1;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;">
            <div style="width:1px;height:18px;background:var(--phosphor-border);"></div>
            <div class="uml-node hi-p" style="font-size:16px;min-width:70px;">Fox</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Code example -->
      <div class="code-card" style="flex:1;">
        <div class="code-hdr">
          <div class="cdot" style="background:#ff5f57;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#febc2e;"></div><div class="cdot" style="background:#28c840;"></div>
          <span class="clang">Java</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          <pre><span class="tp">Animal</span> a;

a = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Cow</span>();
a.talk(); <span class="cm">// "Moo!"</span>

a = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Dog</span>();
a.talk(); <span class="cm">// "Woof!"</span>

a = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Pig</span>();
a.talk(); <span class="cm">// "Oink!"</span>

<span class="cm">// Same variable — different behavior!</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="callout accent-p fragment fade-up" style="max-width:740px;margin-top:var(--gap);">
      When you call an overridden method on a superclass reference, Java calls the <strong>actual object's</strong> version — not the superclass's version.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
